<subSubSection id="1949E031596D5FF9E31AACFAA0539E12" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" type="use">
<paragraph id="45D5365F9AD13793968E7E024EC4E40A" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Use.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F1CDA393B2037EC215F48F3BF96E20F" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">
It is said that if a Masuto dreams unpleasantly about an ancestor (
<normalizedToken id="1ACE3A4A06AF501B24DB43D48A73DD4C" originalValue="“balimo”">&quot;balimo&quot;</normalizedToken>
), then relief is given after a bath with sun-dried 
<taxonomicName id="35A862DAAC9F490A8B801232BD4AD1CB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Coccinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Coccinia hirtella" order="Uredinales" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis id="F424BE5645912A9B1F4027E3735FE459" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Coccinia hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
roots and ironstone in a hole on the threshold of the 
<normalizedToken id="B72C68EA6237B9174EAF624BB62A2700" originalValue="“lelopa”">&quot;lelopa&quot;</normalizedToken>
(the circular fence around the hut) (
<bibRefCitation id="4FF7043D9D6AD2AE9D295CB8C65493E0" author="Phillips, EP" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" pagination="1 - 472" refId="B176" refString="Phillips, EP, 1933. A contribution to the flora of the Leribe Plateau and environs: with a discussion on the relationships of the floras of Basutoland, the Kalahari, and the South-eastern regions. Annals of the South African Museum 16: 1 - 472" title="A contribution to the flora of the Leribe Plateau and environs: with a discussion on the relationships of the floras of Basutoland, the Kalahari, and the South-eastern regions." volume="16" year="1933">Phillips 1933</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="362E01A3EDB1900D9DF55D14E104A16A" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="vernacular names">
<paragraph id="B2DCCF0FDF5EDFB0D6B752057878D267" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<pageBreakToken id="7B2547532D7CF9290A39B7A173BBDBFE" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" start="start">Vernacular</pageBreakToken>
